title: Follow Along 20 Minute Beginner Calisthenics Home Workout
description:
Hey Fam! This follow along calisthenics workout is aimed at helping all those people looking to improve their core and general body strength. Grab your mat, workout gear (or PJ's, im not judging) and follow along with this calisthenics beginner workout to get you started on your calisthenics journey.

Remember, do the reps that work for you. You don't have to go as fast as me or do as many reps as me. The more you practice, the stronger and therefore the better you will get!

Calisthenics has been calling me for years now and today is the day for me to start . I am 60 years old and out of shape and ready to transform .
I’ve watched many videos on the subject and Summer you are the one I resonate the most with and want to learn from .
You are an excellent teacher and very inspiring .
This video is perfect .
Thank You for sharing and for being You .

Calisthenics is a thing of progression. You cannot start doing anything HARD right away, because your body cannot respond to the demands that it takes to do the really advanced things. It's all progression,  little by little daily and constant training. You have to give your body time to adjust to this. It takes years to condition your body, like a dancer or a contortionist etc., You cannot do anything in one day or a few months. Also exercise is a discipline for life, not something you do for a little while, it's forever. One day at a time!
